===Etymology===
From {{der|en|es|platina||little silver}} ''del Pinto'' ("of the Pinto") {{suffix|en||um}}. It was called "little" (or "lesser") silver because the metal was found as an apparent impurity with [[silver]], and ''del Pinto'' for the Pinto River in Grand Columbia where it was discovered.

